HB393 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 Relating to economic development; to amend Sections
4 11-66A-2 and 41-23-252, Code of Alabama 1975, regarding
5 research and development corridors and grants, and Sections
6 40-9B-3, 40-9G-1, and 40-18-372, Code of Alabama 1975,
7 regarding tax abatements and incentives; to remove references
8 to the outdated Accelerate Alabama Strategic Economic
9 Development Plan; to update NAICS Code references to the
10 latest update released in 2022; and to make nonsubstantive,
11 technical revisions to update existing code language to
12 current style.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. Sections 11-66A-2, 40-9B-3, 40-9G-1,
15 40-18-372, and 41-23-252, Code of Alabama 1975, are amended to
16 read as follows:
17 "§11-66A-2
18 (a) The Legislature finds and determines the public
